'''Erik Rhodes''' (born '''James Elliott Naughtin'''; February 8, 1982 – June 14, 2012) was an [[Coming out|openly gay]] American gay [[pornographic film actor]], under an exclusive contract with [[Falcon Studios]]. He played [[versatile (sex)|versatile]] roles in videos and in his private sex life. He was also notable in New York's gay nightlife and social circles; Rhodes used to date fashion designer [[Marc Jacobs]].<ref>[http://gawker.com/354989/marc-jacobs-porn-star-pal-needs-to-shut-up ''Marc Jacobs' Porn Star Pal Needs To Shut Up''] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130125063612/http://gawker.com/354989/marc-jacobs-porn-star-pal-needs-to-shut-up |date=January 25, 2013 }} from ''[[Gawker]]'' February 11, 2008</ref>
Rhodes made his struggles with drugs and depression public for years. He was a blogger and frequently wrote of his heavy usage of both club drugs and bodybuilding steroids. He died in his sleep from a [[cardiac arrest]] on June 14, 2012.<ref>[https://www.nytimes.com/2012/06/21/fashion/erik-rhodess-death-was-early-but-perhaps-not-surprising.html ''An Early Death but Perhaps Not a Surprise''] from ''[[The New York Times]]'' June 20, 2012</ref> He was [[Cremation|cremated]] per his family's request.<ref>[http://www.moloneyfh.com/obituaries/2012/james-naughtin ''Moloney Funeral Home: James Naughtin''] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120620193017/http://www.moloneyfh.com/obituaries/2012/james-naughtin |date=June 20, 2012 }} from ''www.moloneyfh.com'' June 15, 2012</ref> Rhodes's [[HIV/AIDS in the pornographic film industry|HIV positive]] status revelation posthumously in ''[[The New York Times]]'' generated controversy.<ref>[http://blogs.poz.com/oriol/archives/2012/06/erik_rhodes_hiv.html ''Posthumous HIV Disclosure Stirs Debate''] from ''[[POZ (magazine)|POZ magazine]]'' June 22, 2012</ref>
