'''Jamie Fox''' is a Native American musician of the Assiniboine and Grosventre nations, who is a well known performer of the [[Métis fiddle]] tradition of [[Montana]]. She is a member of the Fox family of fiddlers from the on the [[Fort Belknap Indian Reservation|Fort Belknap reservation]]. She has performed widely in the US and in Europe, where she has collaborated with husband Danish traditional fiddler [[Kristian Bugge]] and with Old Time fiddler [[Ruthie Dornfeld]].She studied with Montana fiddler Marvin "Fatty" Morin, learning his bowing technique.<ref>{{cite book|author=Aaron Parrett|date=2016|title=Montana Americana Music : Boot Stomping in Big Sky Country|publisher=[[Arcadia Publishing]]|page=163}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.danishroots.eu/3-fidlers-3-traditions/|title=Traditional Danish fiddler on tour in the US and Canada!|date=24 February 2014|website=Danishroots.eu|accessdate=26 May 2018}}</ref>
